# Noteval extraction workflow (data extraction)

When editing or creating files under `noteval_extractor/output/` (especially `01_`–`04_` markdown, `_page_index.md`, or validation reports), treat this as **noteval / trustee PDF extraction** work.

## Use the Noteval Extractor agent in Cursor

1. Confirm the deal folder already has segmentation: `_page_index.md`, `_chunks/`, and usually `_manifest.md` (and `_chunks_waterfall/` / `*_waterfall*` when Wells Fargo split applies).
2. Prefer the **Noteval Extractor** agent (`.cursor/agents/noteval-extractor-agent.md`) for drafting or revising `01_report_metadata.md` through `04_extraction_summary.md`. The agent is written to follow `noteval_extractor/SKILL.md` and `noteval_extractor/references/extraction-templates.md`.
3. **Before saving `03`, confirm fee rows exist for mapping:** **`### Waterfall table`** (grid deals) **and/or** **`### Disbursement ladder`** (clause-only) with **one amount per payee row**. **Do not** add **`### Valuation-relevant fees`** in `03`; run `py -3 noteval_extractor/scripts/map_valuation_fees.py "<output-dir>"` after `03`.
4. After substantive edits, run validation from repo root:
   `py -3 noteval_extractor/scripts/validate_noteval.py "<output-dir>"`  
   and fix **errors** in `validation_report.md` before treating the run as complete. **`03`:** ladder-only layouts are valid — populate **`### Disbursement ladder`**, not an empty waterfall grid. For merge gates, run with **`--strict`** when configured.

## Operational UI (optional)

The local **noteval UI** (`server.py` on `http://127.0.0.1:8765/`) can resolve paths, segment PDFs, browse chunks, draft with an LLM API, run the unattended pipeline, and trigger validate — it does **not** replace the Cursor agent for tool-heavy editing, but it shortens the mechanical path to a ready `output/<deal>_<date>/` folder.

## Principles

- **One output folder per run**; do not merge page numbers across primary vs waterfall PDFs.
- **Source Text** in deliverables must quote `_chunks/` (or `_chunks_waterfall/`) with **Page N** labels per the templates.
- **`02` scope:** Class / distribution / multi-listing tables only — **no** **Administrative Expenses** (or other **fee**) **grid** in **`02`** (that lives in **`03`** — you **never** “need” the admin grid in **`02`**). When **Principal Distribution Detail** and **Interest Distribution Detail** (or equivalent) are **separate**, merge into **primary** / optional **distribution grid** by **economic Class** (use **`### Tranche by listing`** **`CUSIP`**/**`ISIN`** when **`Multi-listing`** = **Y**); **`### Class balance table (primary)`** and **`### Distribution grid`** **omit** **ISIN**/**CUSIP** columns — **`Principal payment`** from the **principal** table, **`Interest payment`** / **`Interest payable`** from the **interest** table, **`Interest rate`** from **Coupon** / **coupon rate** on **Interest Distribution Detail** when present — else from **whichever** table prints the accrual (often a **third** **Interest Rate Fixing** page) — **not** **0.00** / blanks for interest from a principal-only paste when the interest exhibit has values.
- **`02` principal cash — trace, don’t guess (no magnitude heuristics):** Before treating **`02`** as done, for **each** primary / listing / distribution row, confirm **`Principal payment`** / **`Principal paid`** matches the **Principal Distribution** / **Principal distributed** (or same-meaning) **$** column on the **principal** exhibit in **`## Source Text`** — **never** take **Ending balance**, **Original face**, or **factor** cells as principal **paid**. If the principal exhibit shows **0.00** in that **paid principal** column for the line, **`Principal payment`** must be **0.00**. Do **not** infer from “last number on the line,” token index, or which **$** is larger (see **`extraction-templates.md`** File **02**, **Anti-pattern — positional dollar heuristics**).
- **`02` hard layouts — image / vision escalation:** When **Principal Distribution Detail** **and** **Interest Distribution Detail** both apply **and** **`Multi-listing`** = **Y** (several **CUSIP** rows per class), **`_chunks/`** may not carry reliable **column alignment** or **Note Class** placement — use **rendered page images**, **table extraction**, or **vision-assisted** column readout per **`noteval_extractor/SKILL.md`** (*When to add raster / table images or vision*) and **`extraction-templates.md`** File **02** (*Raster / vision assist*), then **Notes** / **`04`** if amounts were confirmed from images rather than text order alone.
- **Wells Fargo** (when `_chunks_waterfall/` exists): build **`03`** (waterfall + fee roll-up) **only** from `_chunks_waterfall/` + `_page_index_waterfall.md` — **not** from `_chunks/` for `03` amounts or `03` Source Text.
- **Fees in `03`:** **extract** raw fee lines into **`### Waterfall table`** / **`### Disbursement ladder`** (**one payee, one numeric amount per row** — never `54.42; 2,343.73` in one cell) + **Source Text** + **Administrative Expenses grid** when present → **clean up** (non-fees out, correct **paid** vs **payable** vs **available/running** — **`Amount paid`** from **Paid**/**Payment** headers only, **not** **Available**/**Running**; map by **column name** in **`### Column mapping`**, not column order). **Do not** author **`### Valuation-relevant fees`** in **`03`** — run **`map_valuation_fees.py`** for **`05_valuation_relevant_fees.md`**. **Waterfall (A)** / **taxes owed by the Issuer** (or Co-Issuers) must appear as a **non-zero** fee row in the **waterfall table** (mapper → **`tax_gross_amounts`**), not **only** under **`### Other waterfall lines`**. **Administrative Expenses grid:** identify by **section + expense rows**, not only canonical column titles; **`### Column mapping` must explicitly name the payment column** (cash paid this distribution — header text or column index) and map **due** columns to **`Amount payable`**; **never** put the **payment** column in **`Amount payable`**. Grid totals are **audit** only — **`05`** comes from waterfall **Amount paid**. Use **`### Other waterfall lines`** for class cash and structural steps. See **`extraction-templates.md`** File **03** / **05**.
- **`02` Distribution in US$ → primary:** When **Distribution in US$** / **NVR $** exists with **Factor per 1000** / PDD, roll **primary** from the **$** table (economic class / **Total**); put **144A/Reg S/AI** slices in **listing** with **$** from the same **$** exhibit — **not** factor cells (`extraction-templates.md` *Distribution in US$ — primary authority*).
- **`02` SUB / Distribution Summary:** **Dividends** **0.00**, **0%** coupon, **Ending** principal **<** **Beginning** → **`Principal payment`** = Beginning − Ending; **`Interest payment`** **0.00** (do not use **Accrued Interest** / **Current Payable** when that **$** equals the balance drop). See **`extraction-templates.md`** *SUB / subordinated — Distribution Summary*.
- **`03` fees — Subordinated Notes vs management:** **Payment on the Subordinated Notes** / **holders of the Subordinated Notes** are **not** **`subordinate_management_fees`** (requires **management** in the printed fee title). Keep in **`### Other waterfall lines`**; class **$** in **`02`**.
- **`02` multi-listing:** When **`Multi-listing tranches?`** in **`02`** **Summary** is **N**, **`### Tranche by listing`** may be **omitted** or left **without data rows** — do **not** duplicate **`### Distribution grid`** there for symmetry (`extraction-templates.md` File **02**).
- **`02` → database / ETL:** Join **economic tranche** on **primary** **`Class`** to **listing** **`Economic class`**; take **ISIN** / **CUSIP** / **`CUSIP line id`** / **`Listing / program`** from **`### Tranche by listing`** when **`Multi-listing`** = **Y** (`extraction-templates.md` **Database / warehouse mapping**).
- Do not invent amounts or dates not supported by the chunks; use N/A and Notes where required.
- **Non-numeric words in money/rate cells:** In **`02`** / **`03`** **Extracted Data**, **any** trustee/OCR **word** in a money or standalone-rate cell that is **not** a parseable number (not only **Residual** — e.g. **Nil**, **Various**, **Pending**, **--**) → **`N/A`** or blank — **never** pass the literal through to ETL; **Source Text** verbatim. Real rates with digits/**%** (e.g. **SOFR + 450 bps**) stay verbatim (`extraction-templates.md`).
